    "solution": "Let $S_n = \\sum_{k=1}^n a_k = 6n^3$.\nThe $n$-th term is $a_n = S_n - S_{n-1} = 6n^3 - 6(n-1)^3 = 6(n^3 - (n^3 - 3n^2 + 3n - 1)) = 18n^2 - 18n + 6$.\nWe need to evaluate $a_{k+1} - a_k$:\n$a_{k+1} = 18(k+1)^2 - 18(k+1) + 6 = 18(k^2 + 2k + 1) - 18k - 18 + 6 = 18k^2 + 18k + 6$.\n$a_{k+1} - a_k = (18k^2 + 18k + 6) - (18k^2 - 18k + 6) = 36k$.\nSubstitute this back into the desired sum:\n$\\sum_{k=1}^6 \\left( \\frac{36k}{36} \\right)^2 = \\sum_{k=1}^6 k^2 = 1^2 + 2^2 + 3^2 + 4^2 + 5^2 + 6^2 = \\frac{6(6+1)(2 \\cdot 6 + 1)}{6} = \\frac{6 \\times 7 \\times 13}{6} = 91$.",
