    "question": "![Diagrams of two magnetic wire configurations](https://cracku.in/media/uploads/image_4yvtbH5.png)\nTwo identical long current carrying wires are bent into the shapes shown in figures. Shape (I) consists of a U-turn featuring a semicircle where the current enters, loops, and leaves parallel. Shape (II) consists of a semi-infinite wire leading into a semicircle, ending such that the exiting semi-infinite wire aligns radially outward giving zero contribution at center. If the magnitude of magnetic fields at the centres P and Q of a semicircular arc are $B_1$ and $B_2$ respectively, then the ratio $B_1 / B_2$ is _______.",
