    "question": "![Object near a concave spherical refracting surface with marked pole and center of curvature](https://cracku.in/media/uploads/image_STnkdxu.png)\nRefer the figure given. An object of height 2 cm is placed 40 cm from the pole $P$ of a single spherical refracting surface. The center of curvature $C$ is at a distance of 20 cm from $P$, situated between the object and the pole. $\\mu_1 = 1$ and $\\mu_2 = 1.54$ (approximated behavior as 1.5 in intended keys) are refractive indices of air and lens material. The magnitude of the height of image will be _______ cm.",
