    "question": "![LCR Circuit](https://cracku.in/media/uploads/image_B5VnJbN.png)\nThe figure given below shows an $LCR$ series circuit with two switches $S_1$ and $S_2$. When switch $S_1$ is closed keeping $S_2$ open, the phase difference $(\\phi)$ between the current and source voltage is $30^\\circ$ and phase difference is $60^\\circ$ when $S_2$ is closed keeping $S_1$ open. The value of $(3L_1 - L_2)$ is _______ H.",
