    "type": "MCQ",
    "difficulty": "Medium",
    "question": "Let $[\\cdot]$ denote the greatest integer function. If the domain of the function $f(x) = \\cos^{-1} \\left( \\frac{4x + 2[x]}{3} \\right)$ is $[\\alpha, \\beta]$, then $12(\\alpha + \\beta)$ is equal to:",
