    "question": "Consider the following sequence of reactions to give the major product $(X)$:\nBenzene $\\xrightarrow{(i) \\ CH_3Cl / \\text{anhydrous } AlCl_3}$ $\\xrightarrow{(ii) \\ Cl_2 / FeCl_3}$ $\\xrightarrow{(iii) \\ K_2Cr_2O_7 / H_2SO_4}$ Product $(X)$\n$P$ g of the major product $(X)$ formed is reacted with $NaHCO_3$ solution to liberate a gas which occupied $11.2$ dm$^3$ at STP. $P = \\text{\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_}$ g. (Given molar mass in g mol$^{-1}$ H: $1$, C: $12$, O: $16$, Cl: $35.5$)",
