    "question": "$2.0$ g of a bromo hydrocarbon $(X)$ was subjected to Carius analysis, gave $3.36$ g of $AgBr$. The percentage of carbon in the compound $(X)$ is $26.7\\%$. Total number of carbon atoms in the empirical formula for compound $(X)$ is \\_\\_\\_\\_\\_.\n(Given molar mass in g mol$^{-1}$ H: $1$, C: $12$, Br: $80$, Ag: $108$)",
